  "summary": {
    "as": "Passed House amended",
    "asOf": "2007-12-11",
    "date": "2007-12-13T17:26:55Z",
    "text": "Requires Office of Personnel Management (OPM) regulations governing determinations of ineligibility for appointment to a position in an executive agency because of deliberate failure to register with the selective service to provide exceptions for: (1) the appointment of an individual who was discharged or released from active duty in the armed forces under honorable conditions; and (2) the appointment or continued employment of an individual who has reached 31 years of age."
  },
